# Website Project Rules

## Svelte/SvelteKit Projects
- Use SvelteKit for routing and SSR capabilities
- Follow component-based architecture patterns
- Use stores for state management
- Implement proper error boundaries and loading states

## GraphQL Integration
- Use GraphQL for API communication
- Implement proper error handling for GraphQL queries
- Use fragments for reusable query parts
- Implement proper caching strategies

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for utility-first styling
- Follow consistent design system patterns
- Use CSS custom properties for theming
- Implement responsive design principles

## Performance
- Optimize bundle sizes with proper code splitting
- Use lazy loading for non-critical components
- Implement proper image optimization
- Use CDN for static assets

## SEO and Accessibility
- Implement proper meta tags and structured data
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure proper ARIA labels and roles
- Implement proper focus management

## Testing
- Use Vitest for unit testing
- Implement component testing
- Use Playwright for E2E testing
- Test accessibility compliance

## Build and Deployment
- Use Vite for build tooling
- Implement proper environment variable handling
- Use Docker for containerization
- Follow CI/CD best practices

## Content Management
- Use Contentful for content management
- Implement proper content validation
- Use proper content types and schemas
- Implement content preview functionality

## Security
- Implement proper CSP headers
- Use HTTPS everywhere
- Sanitize user inputs
- Implement proper authentication flows